[1] Israel (Bnei Brak)
Date: Mon 26 Nov 2018
Source: The Yeshiva World [abridged, edited]
https://www.theyeshivaworld.com/news/general/1630777/monday-measles-update-more-suspected-cases-in-lakewood.html


An infant has been hospitalized at Mayanei Hayeshua Medical Center in Bnei Brak [Tel Aviv district], after the 3-week-old baby was diagnosed with the measles.

The hospital confirms that the 3-week-old infant contracted the disease from his mother, who was not vaccinated, and was diagnosed with measles. The mother likely caught the measles from another family member who was also not vaccinated.

This is the youngest person to be hospitalized with the measles in Israel.

